"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class initialization**\\n\\nI'm thinking about adding repeated `initializeClass` on multiple class types like `AntClassLoader.class`. I also want to ensure there's an explicit regular null-parent constructor. For `class$`, it could involve something like `new AntClassLoader(null, true)` for testing in isolation to set the field. But if that field is already set by a default test, then it wouldn't make sense to do it. I need to clarify that!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring resource handling**\\n\\nI'm considering whether a resource can be included, especially since the current class is a library. It seems that the resource URL might be accessible in native code. In a native image, ClassLoader resources are limited to what's registered. I wonder if calling `getResourceAsStream` for \\\"org/apache/tools/ant/AntClassLoader.class\\\" could retrieve the resource metadata through an agent. That's an interesting thought, but I need to double-check that this is the case!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_FpT8FTf0IzSvaFTKJjmCnE9j|fc_058403cf174cd2400169fb930f9a6481929b10a68864c6589c", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java/ant/ant/AntClassLoaderTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    void defaultConstructorUsesAntClassLoaderParent() throws ClassNotFoundException {\n        AntClassLoader loader = new AntClassLoader();\n        try {\n            Class<?> systemClass = loader.forceLoadSystemClass(Long.class.getName());\n            assertThat(systemClass).isSameAs(Long.class);\n        } finally {\n            loader.cleanup();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void getResourceConsultsParentBeforeAndAfterLoaderPath() {", "newText": "    @Test\n    void defaultConstructorUsesAntClassLoaderParent() throws ClassNotFoundException {\n        AntClassLoader loader = new AntClassLoader();\n        try {\n            Class<?> systemClass = loader.forceLoadSystemClass(Lo